ch.hevs.isi.db

Class DatabaseConnector

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.hevs.isi.db.DatabaseConnector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataPointListener

    public class DatabaseConnector
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataPointListener
    This class represent a connection to the database in which all the value of the minecraft world are stored This class allows the user to connect to its own database and stores the values of the Minecraft world It implements the DataPointListener Interface

      • initialize

        public void initialize(java.lang.String dbProtocol,
                       java.lang.String dbHostName,
                       java.lang.String dbOrg,
                       java.lang.String dbBucket,
                       java.lang.String dbToken,
                       java.lang.String dbName)
        This method gives the details of the location of the Influx DB to which it connects to. It then initializes the connector
        Parameters:
        dbProtocol - : This is the protocol of access to the database typically HTTP /HTTPS
        dbHostName - : This is the address (IP/DNS) of the database typically influx.sdi.hevs.ch
        dbOrg - : This is the organization of the Influx DB in this case the organization is SIn14
        dbBucket - : This is the bucket of the database
        dbToken - : This is the token (unique identifier allowing access to the database) of the InfluxDB
        dbName - : This is the name of the simulation
